			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I may reevaluate the usefulness of Improved Reclaim. But unless you use Rathe's Son, IR would have a prerequisite of Elemental Pact to be useful without having to carry truckloads of malachite.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
OK here's my argument for why IR > EP
<br />

<br />
1. IR is cheaper
<br />
2. If chain petting, EP is not absolutely essential if you have rathe's son.
<br />
3. IF raiding, in emergencies you might want to reclaim your pet to squeeze off one final nuke. (mobs almost dead, you're oom, and things are going crazy) IR provides 20% of a pet, or 60 extra mana. This is at least as useful as another level of innate enlightment. If you reclaim the current pet (say when he's badly hurt) then unsuspend a second pet, then reclaim that in an emergency that would result in a total of +120 mana over the encounter
<br />
4. IF for whatever reason you have to destroy your current pet and can't suspend him, IR gives you an extra 60 mana.
<br />

<br />
this is versus:
<br />

<br />
1. EP makes it so you only have to carry one stack of malachite, instead of, oh, 3 stacks.
<br />
2. EP makes chain-petting air pet viable. Of course you'll want the less exspensive IR too for this, and if you wanted to chain pet rathe's son you wouldn't need EP.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
